## 2. Full System Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph CLIENT["CLIENT LAYER"]
        WEB["Web App\nReact 19 + Next.js 15"]
        DESKTOP["Desktop App\nTauri 2.0 (Win/Mac/Linux)"]
        CLI["CLI Tool\nRust Binary"]
        SDK["SDK / API\nPython + JS Clients"]
    end

    subgraph GATEWAY["GATEWAY LAYER"]
        GW["API Gateway\nGo 1.22 + Gin/Kong\nJWT Auth, Rate Limiting"]
        NLP["NLP Intent Router\nParse → Dispatch Command"]
        JQ["Job Queue\nRedis + BullMQ / Kafka"]
    end

    subgraph AICORE["AI CORE LAYER"]
        LLM["LLM Planner\nGPT-4o / Gemini / llama.cpp local"]
        VIS["Vision Models\nCLIP + SAM2 + Florence-2"]
        AUD["Audio Models\nWhisper + DeepFilterNet + MusicGen"]
    end

    subgraph WORKERS["WORKER PODS (Python, GPU-backed)"]
        VW["Video Worker\nFFmpeg + PySceneDetect + CLIP"]
        IW["Image Worker\nPillow + OpenCV + rembg + LaMa + Real-ESRGAN"]
        AW["Audio Worker\nlibrosa + pedalboard + DeepFilterNet"]
        EXP["Export Worker\nFFmpeg render + CDN upload"]
    end

    subgraph STORAGE["STORAGE LAYER"]
        OBJ["Object Store\nMinIO / S3 (raw + proxy media)"]
        DB["Database\nPostgreSQL (metadata, projects, users)"]
        CACHE["Cache + Queue State\nRedis"]
        VDB["Vector DB\nQdrant (semantic search + clip embeddings)"]
    end

    CLIENT --> GATEWAY
    GATEWAY --> AICORE
    GATEWAY --> WORKERS
    WORKERS --> STORAGE
    AICORE --> JQ
    JQ --> WORKERS
```

### Architecture Principles
- **Proxy Editing Always**: Store 480p proxy, edit at low res, export from full-res original. This is how Premiere Pro and DaVinci Resolve work.
- **Non-Destructive DAG**: Every operation is a node in a DAG. Nothing mutates the original. Edit history is infinitely rewindable.
- **Stateless Workers**: Worker pods are horizontally scalable. Job state lives in Redis, not in the worker.
- **Keyframe Anchoring**: For temporal consistency in AI edits, edits are anchored to keyframes and interpolated across frames — reducing visible flicker.

