### Phase 1 (Month 1–2): Foundation
**Goal**: Deployed skeleton. No AI features yet. Everything else works.
- [ ] Go API Gateway with JWT auth, rate limiting, Kong plugin
- [ ] PostgreSQL schema: users, projects, clips, operations DAG
- [ ] MinIO/S3 object store with chunked upload
- [ ] Basic Next.js web UI: upload, project list, simple timeline
- [ ] FFmpeg video worker: trim, split, merge, basic transitions
- [ ] BullMQ job queue: job creation, worker polling, WebSocket progress
- [ ] CI/CD: GitHub Actions → Docker build → deploy to cloud
- [ ] NLP parser v0: GPT-4o → JSON operation graph (just trim/split/export for now)
- **Milestone**: Text-to-video-edit demo. "Trim first 5 seconds. Export at 1080p." → works end-to-end.

### Phase 2 (Month 3–4): Core Image Editing + Timeline UX
**Goal**: Beta-worthy image editor. Full timeline drag-and-drop.
- [ ] SAM2 integration: click to select object → mask generation
- [ ] rembg background removal (image)
- [ ] LaMa inpainting / object removal (image)
- [ ] Real-ESRGAN upscaling (image and video frames)
- [ ] React DnD Kit timeline editor with multi-track support
- [ ] Scene detection (PySceneDetect + CLIP) + auto-cut suggestion
- [ ] Color grading: LUT apply, brightness/contrast/saturation sliders
- [ ] Proxy editing: 480p proxy generation on upload
- **Milestone**: "Remove the background from this photo" + "apply LUT color grade" + full timeline editing.

### Phase 3 (Month 5–6): Video AI Features
**Goal**: First AI video editing features. Object removal from video. Style transfer.
- [ ] SAM2 video object tracking (propagate masks across frames)
- [ ] LaMa inpainting on video frames (object removal from video)
- [ ] AnyV2V-style temporal consistency: first-frame edit → I2V propagation
- [ ] RIFE frame interpolation for smooth temporal transitions
- [ ] DeepFilterNet audio denoising (auto-run on every upload)
- [ ] Whisper transcription + subtitle generation
- [ ] Audio EQ (librosa + pedalboard effects chain)
- **Milestone**: "Remove the car from this video" works. "Add reverb to the voiceover" works.

### Phase 4 (Month 7–9): Audio AI + Advanced Features
**Goal**: Full audio pipeline. B-roll automation. Sound design.
- [ ] MusicGen background music generation from text description
- [ ] AudioLDM2 sound effects generation
- [ ] EBU R128 loudness normalization (broadcast standard)
- [ ] pyloudnorm level automation
- [ ] B-roll auto-placement from transcript (CLIP embeddings on footage library)
- [ ] Qdrant vector DB for semantic clip search
- [ ] Batch export with tiered GPU workers (cheap preview → expensive export)
- [ ] GPU result caching (Redis hash → lookup before running inference)
- **Milestone**: Full video + audio AI pipeline. B-roll auto-placement from transcript.

### Phase 5 (Month 10–12): Desktop App + Public Launch
**Goal**: Tauri desktop app. Offline mode. Public beta. v1.0 launch.
- [ ] Tauri 2.0 desktop app (Windows + macOS + Linux CI)
- [ ] Local llama.cpp NLP planner (Mistral 7B, 4-bit quantized)
- [ ] Local SAM2-small for offline object segmentation
- [ ] Native file system access via Tauri IPC
- [ ] Code signing (Apple notarization + Microsoft EV cert)
- [ ] GDPR data controls (export/delete user data)
- [ ] Prometheus + Grafana monitoring
- [ ] Public beta → gather feedback → v1.0
- **Milestone**: Ship v1.0 with full web + desktop app. Offline mode working.

