## 9. Team Composition

**Honest Timeline Assessment**: This is realistically a 3-engineer team for 12 months OR a 5-engineer team for 6–7 months.

| Role | Responsibilities | Required Skills |
|---|---|---|
| **ML Engineer** | All AI model integration, Python workers, GPU optimization, model evaluation | Python, PyTorch, CUDA, FFmpeg, production ML |
| **Backend Engineer** | Go gateway, PostgreSQL schema, BullMQ/Kafka, distributed systems, APIs | Go, PostgreSQL, Redis, Docker, Kubernetes |
| **Frontend Engineer** | React 19 timeline editor, Next.js, WebSocket, UI/UX, Tauri IPC | React, TypeScript, WebSocket, WebCodecs, Rust basics |
| *(optional 4th)* **Systems Engineer** | Tauri/Rust native features, FFmpeg pipeline optimization, media codecs | Rust, FFmpeg internals, native video codecs |
| *(optional 5th)* **DevOps/SRE** | CI/CD, GPU cluster management, Kubernetes, monitoring | Kubernetes, Terraform, GPU node management |

**The hardest parts** (allocate most senior engineers):
1. NLP-to-operation parser — getting it reliable enough that users trust it
2. Real-time preview system for video edits (low-latency proxy streaming)
3. Temporal consistency for AI edits (AnyV2V pipeline)
4. Cross-platform desktop packaging (tons of native dependency issues)

